node.text: Happy 1st Birthday Harley ❤️ @harleyandme my sweet little boy. I can’t believe you’re already a year old. You came into my life when I least expected it time, yet it was a time I needed you most - without even fully realizing it then… and you have changed my life forever. I hope you love this little life of yours and I promise to forever give you the best life I can - So speaking of changing lives, I wanted to share a little bit of Harley (and my) transformation after we spent 4.5 days with @bevilldogbehavior. While there was clearly no shortage of the love I have for Harley, like any other puppy, he did need a little guidance and training and I couldn’t be more thrilled with the progress that was made in even the short time. He continues to spend time with Brad and all of his friends at daycare (puppy school) once a week and always boards with him when I am away for work… Can’t wait to share more with you all about this journey and much much more…. @harleyandme @bevilldogbehavior

node.text:
I’ve always loved fashion. From designing all of my competition leos back in the day to putting together looks for these Olympic Games with @lagabstyle. This red @dior look that I wore on the night of women’s team finals was meant to represent each of the eight nations competing in the event, as all of their flags contain the color red ❤️

AND you can be serious, good at your job, and still love fashion. Don’t let anyone dull your shine ✨
